    "causal_summary": "A verify-fix-verify quality loop already runs LIVE and default-ON on the memory-save path. Its pure scorer `computeMemoryQualityScore` ships at `mcp_server/handlers/quality-loop.ts:392` and exports at `:747`, and the non-mutating reviewer `reviewPostSaveQuality` ships at `scripts/core/post-save-review.ts:573`. That machinery never reaches the authored spec-doc and metadata-JSON surface it is meant to protect. The two metadata JSONs are written by `atomicWriteJson` at `scripts/memory/generate-context.ts:398` with no quality score attached, and `validate.sh` has no rule that scores authored content quality. The result is that the spec corpus that feeds retrieval and AI adherence ships unscored while the much smaller memory surface is scored on every save.",
